{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:proverbs.11",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 11,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 11 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:1",
      "text": "A false balance is abomination to the Lord: but a just weight is his delight.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:2",
      "text": "When pride cometh, then cometh shame: but with the lowly is wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:3",
      "text": "The integrity of the upright shall guide them: but the perverseness of transgressors shall destroy them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:4",
      "text": "Riches profit not in the day of wrath: but righteousness delivereth from death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:5",
      "text": "The righteousness of the perfect shall direct his way: but the wicked shall fall by his own wickedness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:6",
      "text": "The righteousness of the upright shall deliver them: but transgressors shall be taken in their own naughtiness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:7",
      "text": "When a wicked man dieth, his expectation shall perish: and the hope of unjust men perisheth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:8",
      "text": "The righteous is delivered out of trouble, and the wicked cometh in his stead.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:9",
      "text": "An hypocrite with his mouth destroyeth his neighbour: but through knowledge shall the just be delivered.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:10",
      "text": "When it goeth well with the righteous, the city rejoiceth: and when the wicked perish, there is shouting.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:11",
      "text": "By the blessing of the upright the city is exalted: but it is overthrown by the mouth of the wicked.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:12",
      "text": "He that is void of wisdom despiseth his neighbour: but a man of understanding holdeth his peace.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:13",
      "text": "A talebearer revealeth secrets: but he that is of a faithful spirit concealeth the matter.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:14",
      "text": "Where no counsel is, the people fall: but in the multitude of counsellors there is safety.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:15",
      "text": "He that is surety for a stranger shall smart for it: and he that hateth suretiship is sure.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:16",
      "text": "A gracious woman retaineth honour: and strong men retain riches.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:17",
      "text": "The merciful man doeth good to his own soul: but he that is cruel troubleth his own flesh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:18",
      "text": "The wicked worketh a deceitful work: but to him that soweth righteousness shall be a sure reward.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:19",
      "text": "As righteousness tendeth to life: so he that pursueth evil pursueth it to his own death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:20",
      "text": "They that are of a froward heart are abomination to the Lord: but such as are upright in their way are his delight.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:21",
      "text": "Though hand join in hand, the wicked shall not be unpunished: but the seed of the righteous shall be delivered.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:22",
      "text": "As a jewel of gold in a swine’s snout, so is a fair woman which is without discretion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:23",
      "text": "The desire of the righteous is only good: but the expectation of the wicked is wrath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:24",
      "text": "There is that scattereth, and yet increaseth; and there is that withholdeth more than is meet, but it tendeth to poverty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:25",
      "text": "The liberal soul shall be made fat: and he that watereth shall be watered also himself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:26",
      "text": "He that withholdeth corn, the people shall curse him: but blessing shall be upon the head of him that selleth it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:27",
      "text": "He that diligently seeketh good procureth favour: but he that seeketh mischief, it shall come unto him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:28",
      "text": "He that trusteth in his riches shall fall: but the righteous shall flourish as a branch.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:29",
      "text": "He that troubleth his own house shall inherit the wind: and the fool shall be servant to the wise of heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.30",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:30",
      "text": "The fruit of the righteous is a tree of life; and he that winneth souls is wise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.11.31",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 11:31",
      "text": "Behold, the righteous shall be recompensed in the earth: much more the wicked and the sinner.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
